The general sickward houses patients undergoing treatment and observation who are neither in critical condition nor suffering from contagious ailments.

The intensive care ward houses those whose conditions are critical and require constant attention and close observation, as well as patients whose ailments may be contagious and must be kept apart for the safety of others.
The surgery chamber is reserved for the immediate treatment of critically wounded patients. Entry is strictly forbidden unless it has been confirmed that no active procedure is currently underway.
